@node OVERVIEW  "What is Sim4004?"
Sim4004 is an Intel MCS-4 Simulator for use with AmigaOS 3.9. It is delivered
as a set of 3 main programs.

@{b}Sim4004
=======@{ub}
The first, @{b}Sim4004@{ub} is a full GUI-based version that allows full control and
viewing of the i4004 registers, i4001 ROM chips and ports, and i4002 RAM chips
and ports. There is also a fully functional ARexx port that allows externally
developed support programs to emulate hardware devices that interact with the
various i4001/i4002 ports and the Test hardware line. This will not run at
normal i4004 speed, which is why it is a simulator, not an emulator.

@{b}cSim4004
========@{ub}
The second program, @{b}cSim4004@{ub} is a command line version of the main Sim4004
program. This version does not have a GUI and is best used as the engine once
all debugging is done with the main Sim4004 program. This version also offers
an ARexx port with the same functionality as that in the main Sim4004
executable.

@{b}SimPrefs
========@{ub}
@{b}SimPrefs@{ub} is the program used to set the preferences used by both
Sim4004 and cSim4004. This can be called directly from the CLI, from Workbench
or from within Sim4004.

@{b}Features
========@{ub}
 * Central Command Window
 * Register Monitoring and Manipulation
 * ROM HEX Viewer
 * RAM HEX Editor
 * ROM Program Disassembly Window
 * Supports Reaction
 * Global Environment
 * ARexx Interface
 * Popup-Gadget Help
 * Usable on Workbench or Public Screen.
 * Can execute ARexx and AmigaDOS commands.
 * Can launch AmigaDOS shell on public screen for easy access.
 
@endnode

